paragraph.text:
there is  enormous potential for increasing the quantity of electricity produced in the United
			 States
			 from distributed solar photovoltaic systems;

as the market for solar technology continues to grow, the industry will achieve economies of scale
			 that make the cost of solar-generated electricity broadly competitive with
			 the cost of electricity from fossil fuels;

producing electricity from distributed solar photovoltaic systems helps to reduce greenhouse gas
			 emissions and does not result in emissions of harmful air pollutants
			 such as mercury, sulfur dioxide, and nitrogen oxides;
